Daughter of late strong man of Oyo State politics and the Special Assistant to Governor ‘Seyi Makinde at Liaison Office, Abuja; Hajarat Adetola Adedibu has bagged Masters degree from Portsmouth University in United Kingdom. The young Adedibu dedicated the postgraduate degree to her boss, His Excellency, Governor ‘Seyi Makinde whom she said advised her in 2019 to take up a postgraduate study in Public Administration. Addressing newsmen after bagging the degree, the human right activist said she decided to further her studies with the view to widening her scope, knowledge and prepare her for more public service to her society. Adetola added that she will continue empowering young persons and taking the cause of youth in government to a participatory level and humanity in general. The founder of Bibirekosefowora Network Foundation (BINAF) also appreciated her mother, Chief (Mrs) Bose Adedibu and everyone who has been a source of encouragement for her new achievement.